<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Irysangel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I also have a question about this...<P>I know I've asked a zillion times but I swear my luck stinks.<P>1st night we went to Velks, killed some mobs, got some crushed/chipped gems, killed an named by the name of Bledrek who dropped some super warrior pants (36 ac) and a black marble!!!<P>We went there tonight and no named guy, and no gem drops other than crushed or chipped. The ones we were killing were in the hall just above the round room/kobold campsite. Crystalline gargoyles, sentinels and destroyers.<P>Are these not the bp gem droppers? Or am I just hideously unlucky?<P>Is there a better spot to get bp gems at? Anyone very familiar with Velks? I'd really appreciate any input.<P>I chatted with a guy in an uberguild that is wearing the same bp that I can't get my marbles for (argh) and he said his guild has over 35 banked!!! There has to be a better spot to find these at. <P>Help?<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aiien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Siren's in their Grotto, particularly in the big room near the bottom. About 50% drop a bp gem (flawless diamond, pristine emerald or black marble).<P>Also the 57+ rats in necropolis drop these a lot, but it can be tough to get to the rats there.<P>Aiien.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viscera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Very familiar with Velks, and use it as my main group's one-stop shopping point for BP gems. Granted you will need a very good group, but it can be done.<P>Current group is a wizard, cleric, shaman, enchanter, ranger, and a 6th person that we pick up somewhere, any tank is good. Average level is 59, but we've been doing this for maybe two levels now. Any named dog can drop BP gems, as well as Icy Guardians (long respawn, as well as Lord Bob and Velketor's guards), Velium Hunter spiders (<--- mob of choice), large crystal shards (same area as spiders), and other mobs by the castle.<P>In our one group we drop to the lower kobold area, and fight our way to the spider area. Hunters have very high MR, and hit around 215 max. If you are L60 (maybe 59, but haven't tried it), if you pull from a spawn area, only velium stalkers and hunters will come (broodlings will stay). Since I'm the only L60 currently, I do all the pulling.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> The first spider room is the toughest, with 4 mobs, and is really a pain if all 4 are hunters or stalkers. If this is the case, I make sure everyone is buffed to the hilt (Kragg, Marzin, Rune V, Regrowth, etc). and I pull all four spiders. I will DA, and hopefully the chanter can get 1-2 mezzed while the tanks beat on one. I will DB a second time to make sure all of the extras get mezzed. Usually isn't too hard once everything is mezzed. We usually camp in the room near the 3 spectres (you can see them straight up from the room), which has no spawns, and only two dogs next door that are usually killed before we pull the first spider room.<P>All that being said, I've only had to use the DA/DB tactic maybe twice, as usually there are a couple of broodlings in there. The next spider room has two, and the third room has two as well, so if it's just our group, we'll just stagger the spider rooms really well, and pull dogs for experience.<P>I am estimating perhaps a 10-15% BP gem drop rate on hunters, as well as any other gem that can drop in the zone. Hunters can also very rarely drop L55 spells. They are around L51 themselves.<P>Long-winded I'm sorry, but holler if you have any more questions.<P>------------------<BR>Viscera Galen<BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://members.home.net/wire23" TARGET=_blank>Black Tower</A><BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
